The laboratory test of the coronavirus 2019 (COVID-19) and the associated SARS-COV-2 virus includes methods for detecting the presence of the virus and methods for detecting antibodies produced in response to the infection.
The presence of viruses in the samples is confirmed by the OTCR, which recognizes the RNA of the coronavirus.
The test is specific and is designed to detect only the SARS-COV-2 virus.
It is used to confirm relatively recent or active infections.
Antibodies (serology) can be found for both diagnosis and population control.
Tests on antibodies reveal the number of people who have been sick, including those whose symptoms were too small to be treated in a hospital or not at all.
The exact rate of death due to this disease and the level of collective immunity can be determined from such a test.
