During the initial outbreak in Ouhan, China, the virus and the disease were commonly called the "Kronovirus" and the "Hochana Coronavirus".
In January 2020, in line with the 2015 recommendations on the use of geographical spaces in the names of diseases and viruses, WHO recommended the use of the terms “stroke respiratory disease 2019-nCov” and “2019-nCoV” as temporary names for the virus and the disease.
On February 11, 2020, the official names "COVID-19" and "SARS-COV-2" were published.
